I use to experiment quite a bit back then, and I feel like I’m missing some of that lately. I think this winter I’m going to start pushing my creativity again, but put a new twist on this with some of my new found biotope experiences!

If you saw my story yesterday, you got a sneak peak into the 12 gallon long layout! But here it is all cleared up. This is still a work in progress as I’m not sure how I feel about the rock on the right, and want to add a bunch more sand, but it’s getting there! This layout was inspired from my exploration In the Rio Frio in Belize! I asked in the story but can you guess what type of fish I’m going to stock the tank with!?

I realized I don’t think I’ve ever shared a side view of the comp tank! There was a lot that went went into executing the concept, and one major factor of that was a hive visual depth. Unfortunately I only have a standard 75 gallon to work with, and in turn don’t have much tank depth. I conquered that issue by going up instead of back! And here you can see the layers of brick and foam I used to achieve that! Have you ever had to overcome and issue like this? Would love to hear your experiences!

Alright sappy post time. As I sit here back in my hotel room, all I can say is wow…this weekend was a special one. To think it almost didn’t even happen. 

After a series of unfortunate life events that had brought me to a mental low point, I decided to pushed through and attend aquashella in Daytona on my first ever solo trip, not sure what to expect and boy was I surprised but the weekend. Beyond the event being super cool, I finally got to meet some of my long time internet friends in the real, @the_aquascaping_ryno @jeffmiotke @hiepsta @louisvilleaquascaping and @jwdaqua to name a few. And got to meet and connect with so many more amazing and supportive people beyond those noted above. For me that was by far the most meaningful and memorable part of this trip! And so grateful to be able to hang with these amazing and talented individuals all weekend who I’ve wanted to meet in person for so many years!

But to push things even further all of these amazing friends pushed me to jump into the contest when an extra tank opened up, even offering to provide some tools and supplies as I wasn’t prepared at all. Which right off the bat was such an epic experience that I’d love to do more of…But to top everything else off, even with the late start, I some how managed to win best hardscape, and placed 2nd or 3rd (wasn’t determined) along side the insanely talented @jwdaqua and @chantz_the_scaper which I’m beyond honored to achieve and honesty still in disbelief of as their scape was so friggen amazing…

I really cannot express how much I needed a weekend like this, surrounded by such amazing like minded people, and to give me that extra push to support my mental health and get me back in action from what has been one of the lowest points of my life. So greatful for these friends new and old, and the community that surrounds this hobby!  Thank you seriously ❤️
